%N A003500 a(n) = 4*a(n-1) - a(n-2) with a(0) = 2, a(1) = 4.
%C A003500 a(n) gives values of x satisfying x^2 - 3*y^2 = 4; corresponding y values are given by 2*A001353(n).
%C A003500 If M is any given term of the sequence, then the next one is 2*M + sqrt(3*M^2 - 12). - _Lekraj Beedassy_, Feb 18 2002
%C A003500 For n > 0, the three numbers a(n) - 1, a(n), and a(n) + 1 form a Fleenor-Heronian triangle, i.e., a Heronian triangle with consecutive sides, whose area A(n) may be obtained from the relation [4*A(n)]^2 = 3([a(2n)]^2 - 4); or A(n) = 3*A001353(2*n)/2 and whose semiperimeter is 3*a[n]/2. The sequence is symmetrical about a[0], i.e., a[-n] = a[n].
%C A003500 For n > 0, a(n) + 2 is the number of dimer tilings of a 2*n X 2 Klein bottle (cf. A103999).
%C A003500 Tsumura shows that, for prime p, a(p) is composite (contrary to a conjecture of Juricevic). - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Apr 13 2010
%C A003500 Except for the first term, positive values of x (or y) satisfying x^2 - 4*x*y + y^2 + 12 = 0. - _Colin Barker_, Feb 04 2014
%C A003500 Except for the first term, positive values of x (or y) satisfying x^2 - 14*x*y + y^2 + 192 = 0. - _Colin Barker_, Feb 16 2014
%C A003500 A268281(n) - 1 is a member of this sequence iff A268281(n) is prime. - _Frank M Jackson_, Feb 27 2016
%C A003500 a(n) gives values of x satisfying 3*x^2 - 4*y^2 = 12; corresponding y values are given by A005320. - _Sture Sjöstedt_, Dec 19 2017
%C A003500 Middle side lengths of almost-equilateral Heronian triangles. - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, May 20 2020
%C A003500 For all elements k of the sequence, 3*(k-2)*(k+2) is a square. - _Davide Rotondo_, Oct 25 2020
